Interface VehicleSetMoveToXY

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    VehicleSetMoveToXY, VehicleSetMoveToXY
    public interface VehicleSetMoveToXY
    This class represents the SUMO command which allows to set the vehicle move to explicit position.

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        void execute​(Bridge bridge,
             String vehicleId,
             String edgeId,
             int laneIndex,
             CartesianPoint position,
             double angle,
             VehicleSetMoveToXY.Mode keepRouteMode)
      throws CommandException,
             InternalFederateException
        This method executes the command with the given arguments in order to set the vehicle move to a position.
        Parameters:
        bridge - Connection to SUMO.
        vehicleId - The Id of the vehicle.
        edgeId - The Id of the edge.
        laneIndex - The index of the lane.
        position - The cartesian position to move it.
        angle - Angle of the move.
        keepRouteMode - Move mode.
        Throws:
        CommandException - if the status code of the response is ERROR. The connection to SUMO is still available.
        InternalFederateException - if some serious error occurs during writing or reading. The connection to SUMO is shut down.
